    {
      "title": "The definite article ال — sun and moon letters",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Point to a specific thing",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 3,
      "explanation": "ال attaches to the noun: بيت (a house) → البيت (the house). Before 'sun letters' (ت، د، س، ش، ص، ن…) the ل assimilates in speech: الشارع sounds ash-shāriʿ, not al-shāriʿ. Before 'moon letters' (ب، ك، م، ق…) the ل is pronounced: القمر = al-qamar. Writing never changes — only the sound.",
      "culture_note": "The names come from الشمس (the sun — assimilating) and القمر (the moon — not). The alphabet splits exactly in half: 14 sun, 14 moon.",
      "references": [
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Sun and moon letters",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sun_and_moon_letters"
        },
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Arabic definite article",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arabic_definite_article"
        }
      ],
      "drills": [
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} كبير.",
          "answer": "البيت",
          "translation": "The house is big.",
          "hint": "house + the article (moon letter: al-bayt)",
          "display_order": 1,
          "transliteration": "___ kabīr",
          "cell": "moon"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} ساخنة.",
          "answer": "القهوة",
          "translation": "The coffee is hot.",
          "hint": "coffee + the article (moon letter)",
          "display_order": 2,
          "transliteration": "___ sākhina",
          "cell": "moon"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} جديد.",
          "answer": "الكتاب",
          "translation": "The book is new.",
          "hint": "book + the article (moon letter)",
          "display_order": 3,
          "transliteration": "___ jadīd",
          "cell": "moon"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} جميلة.",
          "answer": "المدينة",
          "translation": "The city is beautiful.",
          "hint": "city + the article (moon letter)",
          "display_order": 4,
          "transliteration": "___ jamīla",
          "cell": "moon"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} طويل.",
          "answer": "الشارع",
          "translation": "The street is long.",
          "hint": "street + the article (sun letter: ash-shāriʿ)",
          "display_order": 5,
          "transliteration": "___ ṭawīl",
          "cell": "sun"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} مفتوح.",
          "answer": "الباب",
          "translation": "The door is open.",
          "hint": "door + the article (moon letter)",
          "display_order": 6,
          "transliteration": "___ maftūḥ",
          "cell": "moon"
        },
        {
          "sentence": "{{answer}} حارة اليوم.",
          "answer": "الشمس",
          "translation": "The sun is hot today.",
          "transliteration": "___ ḥārra al-yawm.",
